getLocalName

public java.lang.String getLocalName()
Returns this Windows Event log input's collection name. This name appears in configuration file, as well as the source and the sourcetype of the indexed data. If the value is "localhost", it will use native event log collection; otherwise, it will use WMI.

Returns:
This Windows Event log input's collection.

getLookupHost

public java.lang.String getLookupHost()
Returns this Windows Event log input's main host. Secondary hosts are specified in the hosts attribute.

This Windows Event log input's main host.
